parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the Continuously Variable Transmission (CVT) can cause the vehicle to hesitate or stall, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle hesitates or stalls when accelerating
the transmission slips or jerks
the engine RPMs increase without acceleration
the vehicle loses power
and the transmission fails to engage.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag system can lead to the airbags not deploying in the event of an accident, which can result in serious injury or death.
symptoms: The airbag warning light is on
the passenger airbag light is on
the airbag system is malfunctioning
the airbag sensor is faulty
the passenger seat airbag is not recognized
the airbag warning light is flashing.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden explosion of the sunroof can cause a loud noise, shattered glass, and potentially distract the driver, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Loud bang or explosion sound
shattered glass
hole in the sunroof
and sudden loss of visibility.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the sun visor can cause a distraction to the driver, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Sun visor flops down or becomes loose
blocks the driver's view
and cannot be raised or secured back into place.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The power loss on takeoff can cause a loss of acceleration, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Vehicle loses power or acceleration when taking off from a stopped position
and the gas pedal has no response.
